    {
        "content": "<p>Actually the question for this is```<br>\n/- Problem: For integers n ≥ 3, given two sequences {x_n}, {y_n} satisfying:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>x_i ≠ 0 for 1 ≤ i ≤ n,</li>\n<li>For any 1 ≤ k &lt; n, |x_1 + ... + x_k| + |x_{k+1} + ... + x_n|<br>\n                    = |y_1 + ... + y_k| + |y_{k+1} + ... + y_n|,<br>\nFind the maximum value of:<br>\nM = (|y_1| + |y_2| + ... + |y_n|) / (|x_1| + |x_2| + ... + |x_n|)<br>\nProve:</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li>M = n when n is odd,</li>\n<li>M = n - 1 when n is even. -/</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code>\n</code></pre></div>",
